h1(Introduction)
p("Federal Information Processing Standards Publication 140-2 — Security Requirements for Cryptographic Modules specifies requirements for cryptographic modules to be deployed in a Sensitive but Unclassified environment. The National Institute of Standards and Technology \\(NIST\\) and Communications Security Establishment Canada \\(CSE\\) Cryptographic Module Validation Program \\(CMVP\\) run the FIPS 140 program. The NVLAP accredits independent testing labs to perform FIPS 140 testing; the CMVP validates modules meeting FIPS 140 validation. Validated is the term given to a module that is documented and tested against the FIPS 140 criteria.")
p(More information is available on the CMVP website at: @link[to:"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/index.html"](http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/index.html).)
h1(About this Document)
p(This non-proprietary Cryptographic Module Security Policy for BoringCrypto from Google Inc. provides an overview of the product and a high-level description of how it meets the overall Level 1 security requirements of FIPS 140-2.)
p(BoringCrypto module may also be referred to as the “module” in this document.)
h1(Disclaimer)
p(The contents of this document are subject to revision without notice due to continued progress in methodology, design, and manufacturing. Google Inc. shall have no liability for any error or damages of any kind resulting from the use of this document.)
p()
p(The software referenced in this document is licensed to you under the terms and conditions accompanying the software or as otherwise agreed between you or the company that you are representing.)
