h1[numbered:true](Introduction)
p("Google Inc. BoringCrypto module \\(hereafter referred to as the “module”\\) is an open-source, general-purpose cryptographic library which provides FIPS 140-2 approved cryptographic algorithms to serve BoringSSL and other user-space applications. The validated version of the library is 66005f41fbc3529ffe8d007708756720529da20d. For the purposes of the FIPS 140-2 validation, its embodiment type is defined as multi-chip standalone.")
p("The cryptographic module was tested on the following operational environments on the general-purpose computer \\(GPC\\) platforms detailed below:")
table[border:all, caption:"Tested Operational Environments"]{
  row[kind:header]{
    cell(#)
    cell(Operational Environment)
    cell(Processor Family)
    cell(Compiler)
  }
  row{
    cell(1)
    cell(Debian Linux 4.9.0 \(Rodete\))
    cell(Intel Xeon E5 -2680 \(with PAA\))
    cell(Clang \( 6.0.1 \))
  }
  row{
    cell(2)
    cell(Debian Linux 4.9.0 \(Rodete\))
    cell(Intel Xeon E5-2680 \(without PAA\))
    cell(Clang \(6.0.1\))
  }
  row{
    cell(3)
    cell(Ubuntu Linux 1 8 .04)
    cell(POWER 9 \(wit h PAA\))
    cell(Clang \(6.0.1\))
  }
  row{
    cell(4)
    cell(Ubuntu Linux 1 8 .04)
    cell(POWER 9 \(without PAA\))
    cell(Clang \(6.0.1\))
  }
}
p(The cryptographic module is also supported on the following operating environments for which operational testing and algorithm testing was not performed:)
p(Linux 4.X executing on x86_64 architecture; and)
p(Linux 4.X executing on POWER9 architecture.)
p(As per FIPS 140-2 Implementation Guidance G.5, compliance is maintained for other versions of the respective operational environments where the module binary is unchanged. No claim can be made as to the correct operation of the module or the security strengths of the generated keys if any source code is changed and the module binary is reconstructed.)
p("The GPC\\(s\\) used during testing met Federal Communications Commission \\(FCC\\) FCC Electromagnetic Interference \\(EMI\\) and Electromagnetic Compatibility \\(EMC\\) requirements for business use as defined by 47 Code of Federal Regulations, Part 15, Subpart B. FIPS 140-2 validation compliance is maintained when the module is operated on other versions of the GPOS running in single user mode, assuming that the requirements outlined in NIST IG G.5 are met.")
p(The CMVP makes no statement as to the correct operation of the module or the security strengths of the generated keys when so ported if the specific operational environment is not listed on the validation certificate.)
p()
p()
