h1[numbered:true](Cryptographic Module Specification)
h2[numbered:true](Cryptographic Boundary)
p("The module is a software library providing a C-language application program interface \\(API\\) for use by other processes that require cryptographic functionality. All operations of the module occur via calls from host applications and their respective internal daemons/processes. As such there are no untrusted services calling the services of the module.")
p("The physical cryptographic boundary is the general-purpose computer on which the module is installed. The logical cryptographic boundary of the BoringCrypto module is a single object file named bcm.o which is statically linked to BoringSSL. The module performs no communications other than with the calling application \\(the process that invokes the module services\\) and the host operating system.")
p(Figure 1 shows the logical relationship of the cryptographic module to the other software and hardware components of the computer.)
p()
image[src:"references/docx/.extracted/boringcrypto_extract/assets/image_rId10.png", alt:"figure", caption:"Logical Boundary"]
pagebreak
h1[numbered:true](Modes of Operation)
p(The module supports two modes of operation: Approved and Non-approved. The module will be in FIPS-approved mode when all power up self-tests have completed successfully, and only Approved algorithms are invoked.  See Table 7 below for a list of the supported Approved algorithms and Table 8 for allowed algorithms.  The non-Approved mode is entered when a non-Approved algorithm is invoked.  See Table 9 for a list of non-Approved algorithms.)
h1[numbered:true](Cryptographic Module Ports and Interfaces)
p(The Data Input interface consists of the input parameters of the API functions. The Data Output interface consists of the output parameters of the API functions. The Control Input interface consists of the actual API input parameters. The Status Output interface includes the return values of the API functions.)
table[border:all, caption:"Ports and Interfaces"]{
  row[kind:header]{
    cell[align:center](@text[weight:bold](FIPS Interface))
    cell[align:center](@text[weight:bold](Physical Ports))
    cell[align:center](@text[weight:bold](Logical Interfaces))
  }
  row{
    cell(Data Input)
    cell(Physical ports of the tested platforms)
    cell(API input parameters)
  }
  row{
    cell(Data Output)
    cell(Physical ports of the tested platforms)
    cell(API output parameters and return values)
  }
  row{
    cell(Control Input)
    cell(Physical ports of the tested platforms)
    cell(API input parameters)
  }
  row{
    cell(Status Output)
    cell(Physical ports of the tested platforms)
    cell(API return values)
  }
  row{
    cell(Power Input)
    cell(Physical ports of the tested platforms)
    cell(N/A)
  }
}
p(As a software module, control of the physical ports is outside module scope. However, when the module is performing self-tests, or is in an error state, all output on the module’s logical data output interfaces is inhibited.)
pagebreak
h1[numbered:true](Roles, Authentication and Services)
p("The cryptographic module implements both User and Crypto Officer \\(CO\\) roles. The module does not support user authentication. The User and CO roles are implicitly assumed by the entity accessing services implemented by the module. A user is considered the owner of the thread that instantiates the module and, therefore, only one concurrent user is allowed.")
